{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"f23-serial-scan-driver","questionId":"question-5-rq-05-what-is-the-scan-throughput-ceiling-per-language-file-size-distribution-wh","summary":"Scan throughput is constrained by a serial one-file-at-a-time driver over files <=100 KB, not by parallel per-language workers.","sources":[".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/structural-indexer.ts:1368-1414",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/structural-indexer.ts:1057-1079",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/indexer-types.ts:113-120"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"f24-mtime-only-incremental-skip","questionId":"question-5-rq-05-what-is-the-scan-throughput-ceiling-per-language-file-size-distribution-wh","summary":"Incremental freshness checks compare only stored mtime versus on-disk mtime; content hashes are stored but not used for skip decisions, leaving a same-mtime false-negative window.","sources":[".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/code-graph-db.ts:55-66",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/code-graph-db.ts:380-388",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/code-graph-db.ts:396-424",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code-graph/lib/structural-indexer.ts:1397-1402"]}
